dictionaries to mean pretty much the same as gyped. This one is a little more recent, but thats the point I am trying to make.<br><br>The english language evolves constantly. It evolves much more quickly nowadays because of the access to different forms of media. This doesnt stop people from trying to slow its evolution. I think we will always practice some form of censorship because we feel there is some part of the population that needs protection from what we feel is unacceptable. /shrug. Go figure.<br><br>Gay, nigger, chink, jew, nazi and the many other slurs will not be immune to these evolutionary changes. So trying to &quot;protect&quot; people from the use of these words is ultimately futile. What is more important to me, is understanding how someone is using the word...  what context, what tone, etc. The negative use of these words is what we should watching for and protecting people from not the word itself. <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 3/26/02 2:32:40 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubormwarrior.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Borm Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 2:43:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evolution of language</span><hr size=1> I completely agree and to take it a step further, how can anyone allow an anonymous poster on a meaningless chatboard to cause you real damage through the use of one of these words. I submit, and this is only my opinion, that one cannot actually be hurt by the use of these words - only offended. To be hurt requires some sort of emotional attachment. If your friend, neighbor, parent, etc calls you a name then you can actually be hurt. It is not the name, but the actions of the person that causes the hurt. You cannot have an emotional attachment when no real interpersonal communication takes place. <br><br>Now, if you are offended by some language used, then do not come here. If someone mocks you because you publically gave out some personal information, then shame on you. Because we are completely hidden here, except that which we willingly divulge, you are as &quot;safe&quot; as you allow yourself to be.<br><br>Divulging personal information is kind of like asking your dad to take the training wheels off your first bike. When you skin your knees you might just get less sympathy than you were hoping for.<br><br>Lastly, if you are easily offended and like to tell all sorts of private personal information - join an AOL chat room.<br><br>Borm, just plain mean today!<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uapepsadisticdream.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apep Sadisticdream</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm a Mod!<br>Sadistic Mage Mod<br>Rider of Ankles</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 2:44:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evolution of language</span><hr size=1> Very leveled headed post and very true.<br><br>Alot to be said for what he wrote. <p>Apep Sadisticdream~Leader of Ebon Storm~"The world left in my hands, there's no one left to hear you scream, no one left to see you bleed" "Come and be with me and live my twisted dream"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 3:03:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evolution of language</span><hr size=1> Wrong yesterday is quite often wrong today for some of us. I'd probably take note of who is using the word rather than how they are using it. <p>Zarsiss Razorscale<BR>Iksar Monk, 52nd Scale<BR>Proud Member of Dark Affliction</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 423<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/26/02 3:11:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=481.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Evolution of language</span><hr size=1> Zarsiss - I think context is the best method.  Your suggestion of only looking at the speaker seems to have the problem that it relies on pre-judging a person and bias.<br><br>But on the other hand, the speaker's identity and context are often intertwined. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaelyndimathe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaelyn DiMathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=